oc:kn_57e69aa8 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting up any Google Sheets automation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Design sheet workflows with clear column structures and consistent naming conventions so that automation triggers and formulas work reliably." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent structure ensures formulas like VLOOKUP, QUERY, and conditional formatting work across all rows without manual adjustment." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9167b9a9 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When syncing data from external sources like CRM, payment systems, or analytics platforms" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use append_row actions with deduplication checks rather than overwrite actions for data ingestion workflows, and wrap formulas in IFERROR to handle missing data gracefully." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Re-running a sync should not duplicate rows or break downstream dashboards; idempotent writes ensure data integrity." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_982f382e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before activating any multi-source data aggregation or notification workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify that all external API connections (HubSpot, Stripe, Slack, Google Analytics) are authenticated and that target spreadsheets exist with correct sheet names before activating any workflow." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing API credentials or renamed sheets cause silent workflow failures that may go unnoticed until reports are overdue." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ac6cbe4d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring n8n schedule triggers for sheets automation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Schedule heavy data sync workflows during off-peak hours (e.g., 6:00 AM) and limit task reminder checks to reasonable intervals (e.g., every 15 minutes) to avoid API rate limits." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Google Sheets API has rate limits; frequent polling or large batch operations during peak hours can cause throttling and workflow failures." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e15c2296 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building formulas or n8n workflow steps that reference sheet data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid hardcoding cell references or data ranges in automation workflows; use named ranges or dynamic references instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hardcoded references break when rows are added or removed, causing silent data corruption in automated pipelines." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

